            "answer_text": "I did not sing (at all) until the age of 56. I am at home a lot and sing most every day, and for long stretches and at 58 I pass well enough and post songs that people appear to like.I reckon another year and I will have greater ease.Sing because you are drawn to it, and wish to do it. If it ever feels like pure work, it is not for you at that moment.Personally, I believe that just about everyone can develop their singing voice. There will always be those who like to hear it. If you choose to take a singing instructor, be sure to choose one who caters to the kind of music you like. I do think that is very important! ",
